# User Stories

## _Base Features_

### 1. Create A Post
- As a user, I want to be able to post questions along with being able to see questions posted by other people in my group as well as organization
- Acceptance Criteria:
   -  When I am a logged in user and I click on the ‘Posts’ button in the navigation bar, I should be able to create a new post with a title, a group, an image upload, and a description

### 2. Edit a Post
- As I user, I want to be able to edit posts that I have already created so that I
can modify the post's current text, add new text, or remove existing text 
- Acceptance Criteria:
  - When I am a logged in user and I click on the ‘Edit’ button on the Post Detail page, I should be able to make changes to the title, group, image, and description of that post

### 3. Delete a Post
- As a user, I need the ability to delete a post I've made if the question asked is redundant or inappropriate.
- Acceptance Criteria:
  - When I am a logged in user and I click on the ‘Delete’ button on the Post Detail page, I should be able to delete that post from the application

### 4. List Posts
- As a user, I need to see a timeline of questions so I can see if I can learn more about solving my own problems from others.
- Acceptance Criteria:
  - If the user clicks on the ‘Posts’ button in the navigation bar, then they will be able to see a list of the most recent posts

### 5. Post Replies
- As a user, I want to be able to respond to posts by other people as well as be able to see and reply to  their responses to the things I post
- Acceptance Criteria:
  - If a user is on the ‘Post Detail’ page and they submit a reply to that post, then that reply will be visible underneath that post

### 6. Post Detail View
- As a user, I want to click on a post that interests me so I can view more details about the question being asked and answers to that question
- Acceptance Criteria:
  - If a user is on a post feed, when they click on a post, it will show them the details and the replies to that post
  
### 7. Register a User
- As a user, I want to register an account so that I can access the product services
Acceptance Criteria:
  - If a user enters a valid email address, then that email is saved to the user's account
  - If a user eneters a valid phone number, then that phone number is saved to the user's account
  - If a usr enters a name, then that name is saved to the user's account and will be displayed in many of the application's views
  - If a user provides a password that meets the password requirements, then that password is saved to the user's account and
  will be used for authentication during log-in
  - If the user clicks the "Sign Up" button, then the user information is saved and the user is redirected to the log-in page
  
### 8. User Sign-in
- As a user, I need to be able to log-in to an account so I can access saved data and customize my online experience
- Acceptance Criteria:
  - If a user enters a valid email address and the password associated with that email, then the user will be given
  access to that account's posts and information, as well as the ability to interact with other user's posts
  - If a user enters an invalid email address or an incorrect password, then the user will not be
  able to create new posts, upvote/downvote, or change account settings

## _Additional Features_

### 9. Upvotes/Downvotes For A Post:
- As a user, I should be able to upvote/downvote any posts that I found helpful/unhelpful or agree/disagree with
- Acceptance Criteria:
  - If a user clicks upvote, then an upvote will become visible on the post
  - If a user clicks downvote, then a downvote will become visible on the post
  - If a user clicks upvote after already giving an upvote, then the upvote will be removed from the post
  - If a user clicks downvote after already giving a downvote, then the downvote will be removed from the post

### 10. Sort Posts
- As a user, I need to be able to sort posts in order to filter out posts that don't apply to me and find posts that can help me answer my own questions.
- Acceptance Criteria:
  - If a user clicks on the "sort by newest", then posts will be shown in order from newest to oldest
  - If a user clicks on the "sort by oldest", then posts will be shown in order from oldest to newest
  - If a user clicks on the "sort by votes", then posts will be shown in order from the most votes to the least votes
  
### 11. Upload Image to Post
- As a user, I want to be able to upload an image from my computer or from the Internet as a post along with written posts
- Acceptance Criteria:
  - If a user uploads an image to a post, then it becomes visible on the post
  
### 12. Search Posts
- As a user, I would like to search for content and resources on the forum quickly and easily
- Acceptance Criteria:
  - If a user enters a string in the search box, then a list of posts will be shown that contain that string in the title of the post
